Thanks for opening the issue, @Basti-D!

@rhatdan @nalind PTAL

I am totally fine adding such a feature.  However, I would generalize the new option from `-D` to `--cpp-flags` which would allow for passing the specified flags directly to `cpp`.  In the upper example `-Dbackend2` would be turned into `--cpp-flags "-Dbackend2"`.
